## IV. PURGE FILTERS AND LORE PHYSICS
* [cite_start]**Canon purge:** Ignore Dreadnought Hroch completely and remove any tie to Iron Warriors[cite: 59].
* **Geography:** Setting is Castra Vetera system (**Nine Phalanx**, 3×3 mesh). Chapter world is Noviomagus (civilized forge-world). [cite_start]Combat organization is **ten Vexillationes** (see military hierarchy); do not confuse geographic toponym with tactical unit[cite: 61, 62].
* [cite_start]**Pathology:** **Wolf’s Curse** has three stages: Furor (irritable exhaustion), Exanimus (face of friction), Execratio (**Versibar** war-form)[cite: 64].
* **TIME AND CHRONOLOGY (Castra Vetera — current model):**
  * **Dual filing:** Strategium primary annals use **Castra Vetera (CV) reckoning**; Imperial **~M42** tithe dates are **secondary** and **approximate** (Chronostrife + warp-leg variance). See [`codex-batavi/personae-command-index/events-and-chronologies/master-chronology.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/events-and-chronologies/master-chronology.md) addendum.
  * **Realspace:** Noviomagus and the **Nine Phalanx** age at **normal strategic-depth** time — **no** default “500 subjective years inside = few decades outside” **dome dilation** as story backbone.
  * **Warp:** Approach / egress and **Navigator** theater carry **translation hazard**, **Void Tides**, and mesh weirdness (Rift × pylons × local harmonics). *Ordo Chronos* = **calendar correlation** and **routing**, not proof the forge-world runs **fast**.
  * **Frontier-native bond (Batavi, Elara):** Born or forged in the mesh after the relevant zero point; **service and biography** follow **CV / Chapter annals**, not off-world scroll math. **Optional narrow beat:** catastrophic **boundary / mistranslation** horror — **not** cellular “ricochet rewind” as global canon unless a scene explicitly invokes a **local** exception.
  * **Wolf’s Curse / *Das Erbe*:** Never “healed” by any time trick — DNA-locked states stay regardless of calendar filings.

